	   <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-23099">
		 <div class="commentnumber">56</div>		 <div id="comment-23099">
		  <div class="comment-author vcard">
			 	
			 <cite class="fn">Sara @ Our Best Bites</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		  </div>
		  	
		  <div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.ourbestbites.com/2008/05/brazilian-lemonade/comment-page-1/#comment-23099">07.27.2010 at 12:12 pm</a></div>
		  <p>Atomic Mom- pulverizing the limes is exactly what makes it bitter because you blend the bitter pith into the drink, so definitely avoid that.  If it&#39;s still bitter than it&#39;s most likely your limes.  Limes can be incredibly bitter and that will ruin the whole drink.  Take a taste of the juice in your limes after you cut them and make sure they taste good before you use them.</p>
	
		  <div class="reply">
			 <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2008/05/brazilian-lemonade/?replytocom=23099#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-23099", "23099", "respond", "58")'>Reply</a>		  </div>
